Package org.themasons.covidroombooker.models

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Assistant
    Assistant object is defined as follows: A COVID-19 test assistant is someone related to the university (staff or student) who is volunteering to perform COVID tests. To register an assistant in the system, you need their university email and a non-blank name. The email must be unique and follow the pattern “*@uok.ac.uk”. Print template: | name | email |
    BaseModel  
    Room
    Assistant object is defined as follows: The university has several rooms, and some of the rooms can be allocated to apply COVID tests. A room must have a string code (e.g., IC215) and a capacity. The code is used to identify the room and, therefore, must be unique. The capacity must be an integer value greater than zero.
    University
